[center][size=6][color=#ffff00][b]Perk Shard Checklist[/b][/color][/size]
[size=4]An in-game UI checklist to track all 13 Perk Shards.[/size][/center]

I originally made this mod for my own personal use. After multiple playthroughs, I got sick of trying to remember which Perk Shards I had already collected and constantly having to look up locations in guides.

This mod adds a simple, in-game UI to track all 13 Perk Shards so you never have to alt-tab again. I thought I'd share it in case anyone else finds it useful.

[center][img]https://i.imgur.com/mltbqc8.gif[/img][/center]
[line]
[size=5][color=#ffff00][b]New in 2.0.0: The Automation Update[/b][/color][/size]
[list]
[*][b]Proximity Scanner:[/b] Passively detects uncollected Perk Shards nearby (50m range) and marks them on your HUD.
[*][b]Smart Pause:[/b] The scanner automatically pauses during Loading Screens, Fast Travel, and Menus to save performance. It includes a smart "Fade-In" grace period.
[*][b]Zero-Overhead:[/b] Heavily optimised to ensure it has a negligible impact on your FPS.
[/list]
[line]
[size=5][color=#ffff00][b]Features[/b][/color][/size]
[list]
[*][b]Automatic Tracking[/b]: Passively detects Perk Shards as you play and checks them off once collected.
[*][b]In-Game Checklist[/b]: Manually track or view your progress on all 13 Perk Shards (from the base game and Phantom Liberty).
[*]Progress is saved automatically with your game save (per-character).
[*]A [b]Settings[/b] tab to configure the new Proximity Scanner (Radius, Interval) and optional [b]Lazy Mode[/b].
[*]In-game descriptions, closest fast travel points, and location info for every shard.
[*]A [b]Set Map Pin[/b] button to create a waypoint to the shard's location.
[*]A [b]Teleport[/b] button (in Lazy Mode) to instantly teleport to the shard.
[*]An [b]Unstuck[/b] button (in Lazy Mode) to teleport you to V's H10 apartment if you get stuck.
[*]A counter to see your total collected shards.
[/list]
[line]
[size=5][color=#ffff00][b]How to Use[/b][/color][/size]
[list=1]
[*]Open the Cyber Engine Tweaks overlay.
[*]The "Perk Shard Checklist" window will appear.
[*]Click the checkboxes to mark your progress manually, or let the [b]Proximity Scanner[/b] handle that for you.
[*][b]Proximity Scanning[/b]: Enable (default) this in the [b]Settings[/b] tab to see nearby items on your HUD as you play.
[list][*]You can also adjust how frequently the scan occurs (default 3.0s), as well as the range (default 50m).
[/list][/list][*]To save your progress, [b]Quicksave (F5)[/b] or [b]Manual Save[/b] your game. The progress is tied to that save file.

[line]
[size=5][color=#ffff00][b]Lazy Mode[/b][/color][/size]
For those who just want to get it done, you can enable "Lazy Mode" in the Settings tab. This will show the "Teleport" and "Unstuck" buttons.

[color=#e06666][b]WARNING:[/b][/color] Using teleport functions can be risky. It may cause issues with your save or get you stuck. Use at your own risk and always have a recent manual save!

[line]
[size=5][color=#ffff00][b]Installation[/b][/color][/size]
[list=1]
[*]Install with a mod manager (recommended).
[*]Install [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/cyberpunk2077/mods/107]Cyber Engine Tweaks[/url].
[*]For manual install, download and extract the main file into your Cyberpunk 2077 game directory.
[/list]
[line]
[size=5][color=#ffff00][b]Known Issues[/b][/color][/size]
[list]
[*]When you use the "Set Map Pin" button, the breadcrumbs (navigation path) may not appear immediately. You will need to [b]open and close your in-game Map (M)[/b] for the path to appear.
[*][b]Retroactive Tracking[/b]: The mod detects quest-related Perk Shards using "Quest Facts" even if you picked them up before installing. However, generic open-world shards do not have these flags. You may need to revisit their locations with the [b]Proximity Scanner[/b] enabled to verify them.
[/list]
[line]
